    {
        "content": "<p>I would be tempted to define a map <code>F</code> from the naturals into S by recursion. I'd use <code>hS</code> to define <code>F 0</code> and I'd use <code>hR</code> to define <code>F (n+1)</code> given <code>F n</code>. I'd use <code>hR</code> and an induction argument on m&gt;0 to prove <code>trans_gen R (F (i+m)) (F i)</code>. Finally I'd use a result in the library saying that this map <code>F</code> can't be injective, to isolate <code>i&lt;j</code> with <code>F i = F j</code>, and then set m=j-i. I'm the sort of person who sometimes stops what they're doing and just knocks this sort of puzzle off, but unfortunately I'm giving a talk tomorrow which I need to focus on writing!</p>",
        "id": 218494819,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1606863945
    },
    {
